				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_DMC" class="postlink">APU DMC</a> and <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU#Status_.28.244015.29" class="postlink">$4015 status</a> cover it.<br /><br />Yes, DAC always outputting what's in counter, so last sample affects the starting DAC value for next sample unless game writes to $4011 (as many do at the beginning of a sample).<br /><br />Yes, $4015 enable flag is just for starting/stopping the sample reader.<br /><br />To replay the last sample, clear $4015 bit 4, then set it. The sample's starting address and length aren't destroyed by playing a sample.<br /><br />Yes, only $4011 writes and sample bits reaching the delta output unit affect the counter.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

